column5: Congrats man! I quit for 2 years, then made a big mistake while traveling in Central America... And now I'm struggling to quit again.
20 years ago I quit,  I knew my new born grand daughter should  have a grampa around to teach her things.. I quit that day!!!
Tomorrow is my quit smoking anniversary too. January 10th, 2016.
May 17, 2007; coming up 10 years.  Still miss it from time to time but I'm sooooo glad I was able to quit and stay quit.  Definitely not easy but it's worth the fight.

Congrats all around guys! Locnar give it another go bud, you already know you can do it ?? Feb 28 will be 6 years cig-free for me, and what helped was the realization that the craving and withdrawals begin the INSTANT that butt is done! Every smoke just starts the withdrawal cycle over again.
